CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 15, 1960, pg. 2 reads: "13th Ward Was There - Among the crowd of 20,000 which greeted Senator John F. Kennedy at Gateway Center on Monday evening, was a large contingent from the hustling bustling 13th Ward. Their identification placards can be seen in photograph.  Many persons in the crowd had been waiting in the sun since 3 P.M. Senator Kennedy and his entourage did not reach the downtown area until some two hours later. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Crowd with signs, including one for 13th Ward, waiting for Senator John F. Kennedy at Gateway Center during Kennedy - Johnson campaign
